# NavigAid — AI Smart Cane (Hackathon)

Hackathon project. Deadline: 1:00 AM. 3-person team.

## What it does
Blind cane that detects obstacles via computer vision and physically steers itself away using differential motors.

## Pipeline
```
iPhone camera -> MacBook (CV) -> Pi (decision AI) -> Arduino (motors)
```

## Shared Interfaces — DO NOT CHANGE WITHOUT TELLING TEAMMATES

### MacBook -> Pi
POST `http://pi.local:5000/cv` every 100ms:
```json
{"obstacle": true, "direction": "left", "distance_m": 0.84, "confidence": 0.87}
```
direction values: "left" | "right" | "center" | "none"

### Pi -> Arduino (serial 9600 baud)
Single char: F=forward, L=left, R=right, S=stop

### Arduino -> Pi (serial every 100ms)
```json
{"ultrasonic_cm": 45, "laser_mm": 423, "tilt": false}
```

## Safety Rule
Hardware sensors ALWAYS override CV. If laser_mm < 300 OR ultrasonic_cm < 40: stop/steer regardless of CV.

## Team Roles
- CV (MacBook): YOLOv8 + HTTP POST — `cv/` folder
- Pi (decision AI): Flask server + sensor fusion — `pi/` folder  
- Arduino (hardware): motors + sensors — `arduino/` folder
